TITLE: A traffic stop involving a deputy threatening to shoot a driver in the chest is under investigation, Los Angeles County police say
SUMMARY: A Los Angeles County traffic stop in which a local rapper was approached by a deputy who threatened that the man would "take one to the chest" if he failed to comply with exiting his parked vehicle is now under investigation, according to police.

TITLE: Texas DPS moves to fire Texas Ranger under investigation for Uvalde shooting response
SUMMARY: The Texas Department of Public Safety (DPS) is moving to terminate a member of the elite Texas Rangers unit who had been suspended over the actions he failed to take during the May 24 massacre at Robb Elementary School in Uvalde, according to a source familiar with the process.

TITLE: Times Square machete attack suspect indicted on terrorism charges
SUMMARY: Trevor Bickford, the 19-year-old accused of attacking New York Police Department officers with a machete on New Year's Eve, was indicted Friday on more than a dozen charges, including several terrorism charges, prosecutors announced.

TITLE: Judge suspends law license of lawyer for Alex Jones following Sandy Hook document leaks
Biden awards Presidential Citizens Medal on Jan. 6 anniversary
SUMMARY: President Joe Biden on Friday commemorated two years since the January 6, 2021, insurrection at the US Capitol -- a day he's called "one of the darkest periods of our nation's history" -- seeking to elevate the law enforcement and election officials who held firm against the most serious effort to prevent the peaceful transfer of power in American history.

TITLE: DNC officials recommend giving New Hampshire and Georgia extra time to meet requirements under proposed 2024 calendar
SUMMARY: The co-chairs of the Democratic Party's rule-making arm are recommending that New Hampshire and Georgia be given extra time to take steps toward changing their presidential primary dates.

TITLE: US imposes sanctions on Iranian officials connected to drone program
SUMMARY: The US Treasury on Friday imposed sanctions on officials tied to an Iranian defense manufacturer that designs and produces drones which have been used by Russia in the war in Ukraine, as well as the director of "the key organization responsible for overseeing Iran's ballistic missile programs."

TITLE: Trump lawyers ordered to hand over names of individuals hired to search Trump properties for classified documents
SUMMARY: A federal judge has asked former President Donald Trump's attorneys to turn over the names of the individuals hired to search four properties for documents late last year, a source familiar with the order told CNN.

TITLE: Jack Ma to relinquish control of Ant group
SUMMARY: Chinese billionaire Jack Ma will no longer control Ant Group after the fintech giant's shareholders agreed to reshape its shareholding structure, according to a statement released by the company on Saturday.

TITLE: Foodies left 'devastated' that Ronzoni will discontinue its beloved star-shaped pastina
SUMMARY: Stock up on your starry pasta while you can.

TITLE: 'Maybe we cried too much' over shoplifting, Walgreens exec says
SUMMARY: Throughout the pandemic, major retailers have warned about surging theft and a rise in brazen shoplifting attempts. But a top Walgreens executive now says the freakout may have been overblown.

TITLE: Southwest meltdown may cost it $825 million
SUMMARY: The cost of the service meltdown at Southwest Airlines over the year-end holidays cost the airline nearly $1 billion and will cause the company to report a loss rather than a profit in the fourth quarter, the airline said in a filing on Friday.
